it is because probability really is a difficult and unintuitive idea” (Spiegelhalter 2019).\nSomeone who attended my one-day statistics refresher course expressed disappointment in their evaluation that after a day’s training they did not now feel like an expert.","tags":["statistics","mistakes"],"title":"Mistakes, I’ve made a few, but then again, not too few to mention","type":"post","url":"/post/making-mistakes/","weight":0,"wordcount":944},{"author":null,"categories":[],"content":null,"date":1583107200,"description":"","dir":"post\\","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":1800,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1583107200,"objectID":"a4c5a98a557a91ee0d9ec386389c2499","permalink":"https://medianwatch.netlify.com/post/funding-gender-disparity/","publishdate":"2020-03-02T00:00:00Z","readingtime":9,"relpermalink":"/post/funding-gender-disparity/","section":"post","summary":"The gender disparity in research funding.\rThere is a large gender disparity in the number of research grants awarded in Australia. For years men have won more funding than women. This disparity in success is driven by a disparity in applications, as women apply far less often. Success rates for men and women are relatively close, so policies to reduce the gender disparity in funding should focus on encouraging more applications from women.","tags":["funding","simulations"],"title":"A 2-for-1 deal for female researchers","type":"post","url":"/post/funding-gender-disparity/","weight":0,"wordcount":1730},{"author":null,"categories":null,"content":null,"date":1583107200,"description":"","dir":"","excerpt_html":null,"excerpt_text":null,"expirydate":-62135596800,"fuzzywordcount":100,"html":null,"keywords":null,"kind":"taxonomy","lang":"en","lastmod":1583107200,"objectID":"","permalink":"https://medianwatch.netlify.com/tags/funding/","publishdate":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z","readingtime":0,"relpermalink":"/tags/funding/","section":"tag